  "prompt": "What are some tips on making it through the job interview process at UDR?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for interviewing at UDR:\n\n1. Research the company\n- Learn about UDR's business model in multifamily real estate\n- Understand their company culture and values\n- Review their current properties and recent business developments\n\n2. Prepare for common interview questions\n- Practice discussing your relevant experience\n- Have specific examples ready that demonstrate your skills\n- Be prepared to discuss why you're interested in working at UDR\n\n3. Professional presentation\n- Dress business professional\n- Arrive 10-15 minutes early\n- Bring extra copies of your resume\n- Show enthusiasm and positive energy\n\n4. Technical preparation\n- Know your technical/professional skills relevant to the role\n- Be ready to discuss your past work experiences\n- Highlight achievements that align with UDR's needs\n\n5. Behavioral interview readiness\n- Use STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result) for responding\n- Show problem-solving and teamwork skills\n- Demonstrate adaptability and learning orientation\n\n6. Follow-up\n- Send a thank you email within 24-48 hours\n- Reiterate your interest in the position\n- Reference specific discussion points from the interview\n\nThese tips can help you navigate UDR's interview process more confidently.",
